inventory tracking) and IBM (maintenance) systems. Some replacements could =
launch by 2027 as part of broader cost-cutting. The news triggered drops in=
 IBM (3%) and Salesforce (~4%) shares.</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin:10=
px 0">Is this SaaSpocalypse 2.0?</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin:10px 0"=
>Partially yes</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">AI has materially shifted the =
build vs. buy economics:</p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">AI-assisted =
development (coding agents, better tooling, faster iteration) makes custom =
systems cheaper and faster to build and maintain than before.</p></li><li><=
p style=3D"margin:10px 0">For a company the size of Starbucks, replacing ev=
en a couple of high-cost, imperfect enterprise tools with tailored in-house=
 versions can deliver real savings and better fit.</p></li></ul><p style=3D=
"margin:10px 0">This creates credible pressure on legacy or point-solution =
vendors whose products are clunky or overpriced at enterprise scale.</p><p =
style=3D"margin:10px 0">Starbucks is showing you what other companies will =
be doing over the next several years.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Your jo=
